Overview: Nadia Ritter grapples with the expectations of womanhood during her first week of marriage.

Compensation: Unpaid

Location: Denver Park Hill Area

Characters Needed:
Nadia Ritter: Female, Early 20‚Äôs, values connection and vulnerability above all else

Sarah Ritter: (Voice only) Nadia‚Äôs mom, late 50‚Äôs, well intentioned but comes off strongly

Text 720-305-8418 or email zmchudd@gmail.com with subject ‚Äúnewlywed audition‚Äù and I will reply with dialogue for you to read on camera.

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for a **student short horror film,** and we‚Äôre looking for someone to play the **primary protagonist** ‚Äî a scruffy homeless man, hardened by the streets.

**Role Requirements:**
* **Male, age 20‚Äì50**
* **5ft5 ‚Äì 6ft, preferably with a long raggedy beard.**
* **No dialogue required** ‚Äî this is a physical, presence-driven role.

Actors!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions.

Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free!

LOOKING FOR A COMPOSER

Hi everyone! I‚Äôm looking for a **composer** for a 8 **-minute student short film** called *Space Baby*.

A **sci-fi Comedy / 80s-inspired film** about two college students who find a baby alien and end up raising it as their kid.

The film is already shot, and I‚Äôm looking for someone to create an **80s sci-fi themed score**, mainly for emotional and atmospheric moments. Think inspiration like **Back to the Future, Ghostbusters, and The Breakfast Club** (synthy, warm, nostalgic vibes).

This is a **paid opportunity**.

If you‚Äôre interested, please  email at wagnercarrera138@gmail. com me with samples of your work. Thanks!

items.text:
We are now casting our Spring show Shake Rattle And Roll and looking for self Contained experienced hardworking performers who are keen to take quality musical shows to the community .The 
The show is a celebration to all the greatest songs and stars of the 50s 60s 70s The Beatles ,Elvis, Doris Day, Connie Francis ,Cliff Richard, Buddy Holly and more.
Dates
Rehearsals- 23rd -27th February 
Playing Dates- 2nd March  -1st  May 
We work Monday to Friday (2 x 60 minute shows per day) 
Casting Breakdown We are now looking for strong /experienced Male and Female singer /performers 
The show is a one man/woman show so we are looking for experienced performers that can hold an audience and are looking for engaging vocalist performers.
We are looking for drivers with cars only .
We are looking for performers on all area of the UK -please include bases when sending details.
We are offering 700 per week plus fuel on the road 
Please send details including a singing reel to info@theentertainmentproviders.co.uk

items.text:
Presence is not optional anymore.

Join now a unique opportunity: a two day residency focused on creating raw and atmospheric immersive performance. Designed for artists who feel there is more to unlock in their practice, this residency offers hands on exploration of space, character, and narrative to craft intimate and emotionally charged encounters.
Through guided tasks, improvisation, and sensory investigation, you will finally fill the gap in how the body responds to environments shaped by tension, uncertainty, and resilience in your practice. The work centres on presence, proximity to the audience, and refining how meaningful and transformative experiences are constructed.
Led by Vinicius Salles, drawing on fifteen years of work with Punchdrunk and extensive independent research, the residency offers a rare opportunity to access practical tools to deepen your understanding of how narrative, space, and audience function together as active elements within performance.
Open to all artists at different stages of their practice who are curious about how they can evolve their craft further and interested in expanding their creative approach.
Expect a process that invites risk taking, reflection, and will push your practice beyond the stage at a moment that matters.
RESIDENCY IN IMMERSIVE THEATRE
2 & 3 FEBRUARY
@ THEATRE DELI
PLACES LIMITED
BOOK NOW!
Moment to go further. Master the intersection of body space and the other

Master the intersection of body, space, and the other.
Book Now! https://www.tickettailor.com/events/murmurcreations/2006578

items.text:
üîî Casting Call ‚Äì Short Online Spec Commercial (KODAK / NAHEMI 2025‚Äì26)

We are casting for a 30-second online spec commercial being created as part of the KODAK / NAHEMI Student Commercial Competition 2025‚Äì26, made within our final year of the BA Filmmaking course at UWE Bristol. 

The film will be shot in Bristol in early February 2026 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid with expenses covered, intended for competition submission, portfolio use, and university showcase.

Concept:
The commercial follows a young couple as they prepare for another night living out of their car. Through quiet, everyday moments, the film explores working homelessness ‚Äî a form of homelessness that is often hidden from view. The aim is to gently challenge assumptions and offer a compassionate, human perspective on a reality that could affect anyone. Set primarily inside a car, the story relies on connection, presence, and subtle emotional detail rather than dialogue. The tone is intimate, grounded, and hopeful, avoiding stereotypes and focusing on lived experience.

Roles ‚Äì Young Couple (2 roles)
Playing age: mid 20s
Gender: one male-presenting, one female-presenting
Ethnicity: open

We are looking for performers who feel natural, believable, and emotionally grounded. Think Normal People in feel: quiet intimacy and strong chemistry conveyed through small gestures and shared silences. Actors may apply as a real-life couple or individually.

Apply by: 23rd January 2026

To apply: Please send a headshot, CV or Spotlight/Mandy link, and any relevant showreel or self-tape to Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

TOLD THROUGH QUIET, NATURAL MOMENTS, IT OFFERS CLOSE, HUMAN LOOK ATA FORM OF HOMELESSNESS THAT OFTEN GOES UNSEEN. CASTING CALL for a 10-minute short FILM !!
We are looking for actors for our short film!

Please send your headshot, resume, and demo reel to jooheekim.film@gmail.com

Project name: After The Rain
Director: Joohee Kim
Shoot Dates: Feb 2026

This film explores staying vs. leaving, language barriers, and emotional distance through an intimate, dialogue-driven structure.
Most scenes are two-handers, focusing on subtle emotional shifts rather than dramatic action.

NOTES
* Low-budget / passion project
* Meals & screen credit provided
* Ideal for actors interested in voiceover, minimalist acting, and arthouse storytelling

Most scenes are two-handers, focusing on subtle emotional shifts rather than dramatic action.

NOTES
* Low-budget / passion project
* Meals & screen credit provided
* Ideal for actors interested in voiceover, minimalist acting, and arthouse storytelling

items.text:
PAID: Looking for a production assistant for documentary.
Hi everyone! My name is Bryanna Reynolds and I am an independent filmmaker based here in Los Angeles but originally from Australia. I am producing my first short film "The Last Eight" and I am looking for a production assistant.

The documentary tells the story of the city of Burbank Community coming together over the course of 2025 and building a float for the 137th Rose Parade in Pasadena, California. 

The float is a pirate ship and the overall film has a sense of adventure, urgency and emotional reflection of people coming together. 

I need a production assistant to help me with festival research, submission, and general outreach to communities and people involved in the float. The job can be remote. 

Thank you so much! I look forward to connecting with you all! 

Please reach out on the official page The Last Eight or on Instagram @thelasteight_film

topComments.text: As a fellow producer, having a solid festival submission plan is the job of the producers, not a PA. It's a very important part of the film's promotion and understanding the ins and outs is more complicated than it appears at first glance. Congrats on your film!
I sent a message through the official fb page

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonat√≥w ‚Äò‚ÄôGrupa1940‚Äô‚Äô poszukuje ** mƒô≈ºczyzny** **bez zarostu** w **wieku 23 ‚Äì 40** lat o wzro≈õcie 170 - 180  cm, pas 90 - 100 i **obw√≥d klatki do 90/100cm** do roli Starszego sier≈ºanta sztabowego ( wartownika) Himmlera. Szukamy kogo≈õ z **Gliwic lub okolic**: Zabrze, Katowice najdalej gdy≈º odleg≈Ço≈õƒá do tej roli ma znaczenie. Kostium jest w kolorze czarnym. Same zdjƒôcia bƒôdƒÖ realizowane na terenie Gliwic. Postaƒá ta bƒôdzie mieƒá kwestie po niemiecku.

 

**Na wiosnƒô roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjƒôc do tego **projektu. Bƒôdziemy realizowaƒá mini serial oparty o wƒÖtki grupy okultystycznej ‚Äô‚Äô**Ahnenerbe‚Äô**‚Äô kt√≥ra chce zdobyƒá s≈Çynne artefakty ale w tym kto≈õ im chce przeszkadzaƒá. Projekt bƒôdzie  siƒô sk≈Çadaƒá z 6 odcink√≥w po 10/12 minut ka≈ºdy. Bƒôdziemy te≈º sukcesywnie dodawaƒá inne og≈Çoszenia zwiƒÖzane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjƒôcia aktualne. Na zdjƒôciu powy≈ºej osoba bƒôdzie mieƒá podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materia≈Çy sƒÖ z naszej sesji.** Nie bƒôdzie to zlecenie p≈Çatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 za≈Ço≈ºyli≈õmy sw√≥j kana≈Ç na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych plan√≥w ≈ºeby mo≈ºna by≈Ço zobaczyƒá jak to u nas wyglƒÖda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

 

Wiƒôcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukaza≈Ç zbrodnie i sam fakt i≈º by≈Ça w pe≈Çni z≈Ça. W produkcji znajdƒÖ siƒô osoby, kt√≥re bƒôdƒÖ chcieƒá walczyƒá i potƒôpiaƒá te wielkie z≈Ço jakim by≈Ç nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawo≈Çywanie domnienawi≈õci", ¬ß3 - nie narusza prawa proponujƒÖc przedmiot do cel√≥w historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

items.text:
Have you ever wondered what it really feels like to act?
To step into a scene, speak truthfully, and feel fully alive on stage?

‚ú® A Taste of Acting is a fully immersive workshop designed for:
‚úî Beginners
‚úî The curious
‚úî Anyone secretly dreaming of acting ‚Äî or ready to pursue it seriously

This is a hands-on, practical experience where you‚Äôll be on your feet, learning the core techniques professional actors use ‚Äî not just watching, but doing.

üî• PLUS a BONUS session:
Mastering Theatre Auditions
Because once the spark is lit, the next step is knowing how to audition with confidence.

üé≠ You‚Äôll learn:
‚Ä¢ The foundations of acting technique
‚Ä¢ How to connect truthfully to text and emotion
‚Ä¢ What directors actually look for
‚Ä¢ How to prepare and perform in a theatre audition

üë• Only 8 places available
We keep groups small so every participant is seen, supported, and guided.

üí∞ 49 PLN
‚è± 2 hours total

If acting has been calling you ‚Äî this is your sign to answer.

items.text:
Altarena Playhouse (Alameda, CA) is holding auditions for *‚ÄòNight Mother *by Marsha Norman, Directed by ShawnJ West

 

Performance Dates: May 29th through June 28th     

(Fridays/Saturdays at 7:30 pm, and Sundays at 2:00 pm)

 

SHOW SYNOPSIS:

Thelma Cates is a mother and widow who lives with her daughter, Jessie. Jessie is the divorced mother of a troubled son who struggles with life as an unemployed epileptic. She confesses to her mother that she is going to take her life. Tonight. As Mama pleads with her to reconsider her decision, old secrets are revealed, and long-ignored feelings rise to the surface. The mother-daughter bond between Jessie and Mama becomes stronger and lovelier than ever, making it possible for Jessie to end her noisy, cluttered existence, and take a quieter, calmer path with closure and love.

 

AUDITION DATES:

Monday, January 19th at 7:00pm and Saturday, January 24th at 1:00pm, by appointment

 

Callbacks: Monday, February 2nd, 7-10 pm, by invitation

 

Rehearsals begin April 25, 2026 at 11:00 am

 

Auditions will be held at the Altarena Playhouse, 1409 High Street, Alameda

 

Performers of all races and ethnicities are encouraged to audition.

 

Non-AEA only. $500 Reimbursement for expenses

 

 

CHARACTER DESCRIPTIONS:

THELMA ‚ÄúMAMA‚Äù CATES (Female, 60s)

Warm, talkative, and steeped in the routines of her home life, Thelma is a woman who uses chatter, caretaking, and small comforts to keep the world steady. Beneath her practical exterior, she carries deep anxieties, regrets, and unspoken guilt that surface as the night unfolds. Actors should bring emotional dexterity, humor grounded in truth, and the ability to navigate sharp tonal shifts as Mama confronts an unthinkable situation with both denial and fierce love.

 

JESSIE CATES (Female, 40s)

Direct, methodical, and emotionally contained, Jessie is a woman who has lived with chronic illness, disappointment, and a profound sense of futility. She speaks plainly and acts with quiet determination, revealing a grounded pragmatism rather than melodrama. Actors should bring a nuanced stillness, clarity of intention, and the ability to reveal the powerful internal life beneath Jessie‚Äôs calm, steady presence.

 

To sign up and for audition sides, visit:  [https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night](https://www.signupgenius.com/go/9040F4FAFAB28A2F94-61249455-night)

 

Please contact Katina at [artisticdirector@altarena.org](mailto:artisticdirector@altarena.org) should you have any questions.

Dear friends,

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly known as The Colorado Film School), invites all actors to Open Auditions for our Spring 2026 Semester!

We really need you to help our students tell their stories with the magic of Cinema!

All ages are welcome!

 

Actors can sign up by scanning this flyer. Please share this information with your friends! 

With the Open Auditions, also we will have satellite auditions on the same days! It will be first-come first-serve situation. Actor will go to a room and sign up to cold read for the specific production. There could possibly be around 10 more different productions to cast!

Looking forward to seeing you all!

Title: A Bucket of Blood (Re-imagining)

Genre: Horror

Logline: Damien is a 17-year-old student struggling with alcoholism and a rough home life. After a party, a classmate and him are attacked by a masked killer who is trying to make the ultimate art project with carnage. Damien is forced to face this killer and his own addiction. To survive, he must find a way to reclaim his life from this killer and the bottle of a bottle.

Role(s): 

Aylssa (Female Early 20s): Damien‚Äôs older sister. She tries to check in on Damien‚Äôs well-being from a distance.

Amelia (Female 15-20s): Damein‚Äôs ex-girlfriend. Despite their breakup, she cares deeply for his safety.

Mario (Male 15-20s): Damien‚Äôs close friend who attempts to support Damien during hard times.

Detective Liese (Female Adult): The investigator handling the ‚ÄúBucket of Blood‚Äù serial murders. Damien works closely with her to figure out the killer is counting down to something big.

Killer (Male): Looking for a male around 5ft 10 inches, 115 - 140 pounds, could be taller. The killer is a masked assailant who wears a paint-splattered mask. He‚Äôs harvesting victims to create the ultimate art piece.

Production Company: Christopher Roberts, Eggs and Bacon Productions

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: eggsandbaconsbusiness@gmail.com

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Unpaid, the role of the killer can be negoitated

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please reach out for further information.

Shooting Schedule: TBD

Filming Location: All roles can be done via online, the role of the killer is IN-PERSON.

**CASTING CALL:**

Bellingham, WA. based independent producer / director is looking for talent for a micro budget, non union, short film.

**PROJECT DESCRIPTION:** Comedy short about an office interview with unexpected consequences.

**PRODUCER:** Jerome Wallerstein

**FILMING DATES**: March or April 2026

**FILMING LOCATION: **Deming, WA

**FILMING DURATION:** 1-2 days.

**UNION STATUS: **non-SAG-AFTRA

**USAGE:** Web, Social, in perpetuity, non-exclusive; submission to film festivals intended

**SUBMISSION DEADLINE:** February 5th, 2026

**TO APPLY: Please send headshot / photos, link to your reel or video snippets, to**

**[wallerstein@sbcglobal.net](mailto:wallerstein@sbcglobal.net)**

**with the title "Just A Few Questions" in the subject line.**

**SYNOPSIS: **During an initial job interview, a potential candidate is obsessively fixated on a subject that the staid and conservative management team is wholly unprepared to address.

**ROLES:**

**Gender specific Male roles:**1) Youngish-looking male who can pass for early to mid 20‚Äôs; well spoken, quick, but gives the vibe of involvement with vaguely illicit activities, 2) Two males who can pass for their late late 30‚Äôs ‚Äì late 40‚Äôs, somewhat conservative and staid, but hoping to disaffirm that impression. All roles require comedic timing and pacing and ability to play off each other.

**Rate: NON-PAID, compensation for travel available. Meals provided.**

EXCITING NEWS!

I'm thrilled to share my screenplay/book EDDIE'S BACK - A gripping story that I believe would make a FANTASTIC MOVIE. 

I have already WRITTEN AND COPYRIGHTED THE SCREENPLAY, so it's ready to go! Now I'm reaching out to PRODUCTION COMPANIES , LITERARY AGENTS , FILM AGENTS AND #DIRECTORS who might be interested in bringing this story to life on the big screen.

EDDIE'S BACK - May 1963, Eddie a popular teenager is intentionally hit by a car, which leaves him in a coma. It's 2026, Eddie wakes up. He is shocked and disappointed at what he sees. Until the ghost of JFK visits him and INSPIRES HIM to make a difference.

Now Eddie 79 years young, realizes why he was KEPT ALIVE and what he has to do.

However, a senior Senator with an agenda of his own is watching Eddie's every move and is prepared to stop Eddie's mission at any cost.

DREAM CAST (just imagining!)

#HarrisonFord - #CandyClark - #PaulLeMat - #RichardDreyfuss - #CharlesMartinSmith - #BradleyCooper -#MatthewMcConaughey - #MargotRobbie - #TaylorSwift - #AnneHathaway - #ParisHilton - #JordonHudson - #LaurenSanchez - #AmberHeard - #KrisJenner  #SydneySweeney - #TinaLouise - #CarolBurnett - #ColinHanks - #SenatorJohnKennedy 

DIRECTOR - #RonHoward 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE AND HOPING TO GET EDDIE'S BACK - INTO THE RIGHT HANDS!

TAGGING TOP AGENCIES: 

@ImageEntertainment - @IndependentArtistGroup - #WilliamMorrisEndeavor - #VerveTalentandLiteraryManagement - #CreativeArtistsAgency - #TheWayneAgency. And Indie powerhouses like: #A24 - #AnnapurnalPictures - #PlanBEntertainment - #BlumHouseProductions - #KillerFilms - #Neon - #FilmNation - #BleeckerStreet - #ElaraPictures - #BigBeach - #APAAgency - #UnitedTalentAgency - #GershAgency - #ArtistsFirst - #IFCFilms - #SonyClassics - #LionsGate 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - Just putting it out there and hoping to get - EDDIE'S BACK into THE RIGHT HANDS!

PRODUCTION COMPANIES I ADMIRE:

#SONYPICTURES - #WARNERBROSDISCOVERY - #IMAGEENTERTAINMENT - #WALTDISNEYPICTURES - #HelloSunshine - #BadRobot - #FifthSeason 

PRODUCERS - I'd love to work with:

#MarkCiardi - #MattDamon - #MarkWahlberg #WillFerrell - #TomHanks - #JeffBezos - #ElonMusk - #ChristineVachon - #TeddySchwarzman - #NinaYangBongiovi #LenaWaithe 

NO OFFICIAL TIES - JUST PUTTING IT OUT THERE. HOPING TO GET (EDDIE'S BACK) INTO THE RIGHT HANDS.

I'd also like to catch the eye of DIRECTORS like: #StevenSpielberg - #RonHoward - #StevenSoderbergh - #ToscaMusk - #RyleeScott - #SofiaCoppola - #GeorgeLucas - #BenStiller 

Their storytelling I admire deeply.

No Official ties - Just hoping to catch the eye of these incredible teams.

If you know someone in the film or media who might love this concept, please feel free to REACH OUT or SHARE THIS POST. 

IMDB.ME  https://pro.imdb.com/name/nm4381966

LET'S MAKE MOVIE MAGIC HAPPEN!

#EDDIE'S BACK #BooktoFilm #Screenplayready #FilmAdaptation #Moviepitch #Filmmakers #Independantfilm #IndieCinema #literaryagents

**WEITERBILDUNG IM BEREICH FILMSCHNITT MIT EXPERT*INNEN AUS DER FILMBRANCHE **(ONLINE):

Vom 09.02.2026 - 22.05.2026 findet in der Schnitt-Akademie Berlin der n√§chste gro√üe Kompaktkurs Filmschnitt f√ºr alle statt, die sich in den technischen und dramaturgischen Bereichen des Filmschnitts weiterbilden wollen: https://www.schnitt-akademie.de/kompaktkurse.php?KursID=100

Der Kurs findet komplett in Form von Online-Unterricht statt, man kann also von jedem beliebigen Ort aus daran teilnehmen. Er dauert 3,5 Monate, Mo-Fr jeweils von 09:00-17:00. 

**Die Weiterbildung kann mit einem Bildungsgutschein der Agentur f√ºr Arbeit (100%-F√∂rderung, auch f√ºr Firmen und Besch√§ftigte) oder durch die EU-F√∂rderung KOMPASS (90%-F√∂rderung, f√ºr Solo-Selbst√§ndige) finanziert werden .** 

Inhalte des Kurses: 

- AVID Mediacomposer

- DaVinci Resolve

- Adobe Premiere Pro

- After Effects

- Spiel- u. Dokumentarfilmschnitt

- Schnitt von TV-News und Reportagen

- Codecs, Imports, Exports und Workflows

- Schnitt u. Sound

- Dramaturgie, Rhythmus und Gestaltung

- Schnitt-Assistenz

# **Casting Call ‚Äì Vancouver Laser & Skin Care Centre**

Hi everyone!
We are currently casting talent for **vertical ads **to promote our upcoming **February & March campaign**.

## **Roles Needed**
* **2 talents (male & female)**
* **Age:** 25‚Äì35
* **Ethnicity:** Caucasian or East Asian
* **Language:** Native-level English fluency
* **Preferred (not required):** Experience with social media content, beauty industry, or ad shoots

##  **Project Details**
* **Deliverables:** 6‚Äì9 vertical videos (approx. 15-second ads)

* **$300 flat rate**
* **One BBL or PicoWay Treatment**
* **Snacks & coffee provided** 

## **How to Apply**

Please email the following to **ben@vancouverlaser.com**
**Subject line:** *February/March Campaign + [Your Name]*
* Headshot
* Resume
* Demo videos (if available)

**Please note that private messages will not be replied to**.

If you have any questions, feel free to reach out.
We look forward to your submissions!

items.text:
**CASTING CALL ‚Äì AMBER (LEAD ROLE)**

**Short Film | Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller**

Hello everyone,

We‚Äôre reopening casting for the **lead role of Amber** due to an unexpected last-minute change. The actress previously cast had to step away for a paid commitment. There are no hard feelings ‚Äî we completely understand and wish her the best. This does, however, mean we‚Äôre reaching out again in hopes of finding the right person to step in and collaborate with us.
**PROJECT DETAILS**

**Project:** Short Film
**Genre:** Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller
**Shoot Location:** Lower Mainland, BC
**Shoot Date:** **Sunday, January 18th**
**Compensation:** Volunteer / Passion Project

All preparation is already in place. If you‚Äôre available and able to step in, you would genuinely be **saving the day** and helping us keep the shoot on track.
**ROLE: AMBER**

**Age Range:** 27‚Äì40
**Gender:** Female
**Ethnicity:** Open / Race-agnostic
**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she begins to rely on it too heavily. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.
**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a **subtle, internal performance**. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and a loss of trust in her own judgment.
**KEY TRAITS**
* Intelligent
* Controlled
* Ambitious (not arrogant)
* Emotionally guarded
* Increasingly detached
**AUDITION / SUBMISSION**

Self-tape audition
One dramatic scene (sides will be provided)

Please submit:
* Headshot
* Resume (if available)

**Email:** soultales.ca@gmail.com
**Subject:** AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

items.text:
Hi, there! My name is Zo√´ - I'm an American actor living in Edinburgh, and I am beginning to offer private individual or group acting coaching sessions. I graduated with my MFA degree in Acting for the Stage and Screen last year, and before moving to Scotland, I lived in Los Angeles, CA for 7 years, where I earned my Bachelor of Arts degree in Acting. I've been acting for almost 20 years now and have studied at the University of Southern California's School of Dramatic Arts (LA), The National Theatre Institute (CT & UK), The Storyteller's Conservatory (LA), The Actor's Gym (NYC), and Edinburgh Napier University. 

I have a strong and extensive background on both stage and screen, and I'm keen to work with individuals who are looking to develop their audition technique. I have years of experience working alongside other actors on self tapes and stage auditions, and I have developed a personal group of friends who come to me for help with auditions. My experience and confidence working with friends has inspired me to try to help others. 

If you or anyone you know might be interested, please feel free to send me a DM. I am open to working with people online or in person, and I'm happy to offer one-off sessions or consistent sessions. 

For samples of my own acting work, including my showreel and voice over reels, you can view my Spotlight profile here: https://app.spotlight.com/5816-4509-4543

Additionally, I have just launched my own production company last year with my partner. It's called Muddrag Productions, and I am producing, directing, and starring in our first project currently in development. My experience working as a director for both the stage and screen has bolstered my ability to help other actors from a different perspective, understanding, and expectation.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

Best,

Zo√´

**Casting Call - 1970s Biographical Feature Film**

For a new biographical feature film set in the 1970s, we are looking for **MEN aged approx. 20-35, up to 180 cm max., **an athletic build. In role** future MILITARY PERSONNEL**.

Gentlemen of the following origins are particularly welcome:
* **CUBANS**
* **MONGOLIANS**
* **BULGARIANS**
* **HULGARIANS**

**Shooting Days:**
* February 5 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 18 ‚Äì shooting in Warsaw
* March 26 ‚Äì shooting in Pi≈Ça (transport and hotel provided)
* May 1 ‚Äì shooting likely in Warsaw (TBC)

**Rate: 450 PLN per shooting day**

**Characterization Guidelines:**
* Absolutely no tattoos
* Hair must be short, but cut without the use of clippers
* No facial hair (clean-shaven)
* Athletic build

**Please send applications to:** **ewelina.wika@podtytulem.pl**
**Subject Line:** **KKZ**
**Email Content:** Name and surname, age, phone number, city/town of residence, nationality + measurements: height, chest, waist, hips, clothing and shoe size.
**Attachment:** **PHOTO OF FACE AND FIGURE: taken only on the day of application + profile photo**

**FACE PHOTO** ‚Äì portrait selfie in daylight, straight-on, looking into the lens. No filters. No glasses. No head covering.
**FIGURE PHOTO** ‚Äì in clothing that shows the outline of the figure.

Hi Everyone!

I'm excited to share that the new casting platform, Castingly, is almost at **600 members!** As we prepare to meet with casting directors to showcase the site, I'm actively seeking actors interested in being featured as "example profiles." If you‚Äôd like to participate, please comment below and let me know!

To effectively show off all the site's capabilities, we need users to complete **100% of their profiles.** 

If you're not interested in being showcased but still want to explore the site, you can check us out at [www.castingly.com](http://www.castingly.com/). 

**Membership is free through 2026!** We'll also be rolling out casting breakdowns within the next few weeks. Feel free to reach out if you have any questions!

***FREE SOLO SHOW CLASS THIS SATURDAY ***

Hello Acting Community!

Are you curious about creating a ONE PERSON SHOW?

Then you do not want to miss this 100% FREE, 100% AWESOME solo theatre class "The Art of Creating the One Person Show" commencing THIS SAT JANUARY 17th @10AM (PST)/12pm (CST)/1pm (EST) via Zoom.

RSVP HERE: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I have been teaching this ongoing FREE class for over a decade and I have been working in the genre of Solo Theatre for over 20 years. I have directed & developed well over 175 solo shows and toured successfully with my own award-winning solo shows, and I would be honored and excited to help guide YOU into your own success as a Solo Artist.

**ALL EXPERIENCE LEVELS WELCOME**, and no material needed to bring to the virtual class as I always provide a writing prompt. If you do have a solo excerpt you wish to share, that option will be available too.

All you need to attend this Zoom class is a willingness to explore, something to write with and on, and an RSVP here: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I truly hope you will join the Soaring Solo Community and I for this fabulous virtual event. Let's turn your solo show dreams into an amazing reality!

Jessica

Founder & CEO of Soaring Solo Studios

Blogger for NoHo Arts

Director/Teaching Artist for the LA Women's Theatre Festival

Director & Developer of over 175 solo shows

All you need to attend this Zoom class is a willingness to explore, something to write with and on, and an RSVP here: [https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/](https://www.soaringsolostudios.com/free-one-person-play-class/)

I truly hope you will join the Soaring Solo Community and I for this fabulous virtual event. Let's turn your solo show dreams into an amazing reality!

Jessica

Founder & CEO of Soaring Solo Studios

Blogger for NoHo Arts

Director/Teaching Artist for the LA Women's Theatre Festival

Director & Developer of over 175 solo shows

Casting Notice: REAL WOMEN HAVE CURVES (THE PLAY)
Venue: Casa 0101 Theater, Los Angeles, CA
Project Type: Theatre
Union Status: AEA (non-union talent will also be considered)

Auditions by appointment only - SUBMIT HEADSHOT & RESUME TO Casting@casa0101.org by 9PM PST 1/29/2026 - please submit only once

Seeking strong cast that is fully bilingual (Spanish / English) for this new production of Real Women Have Curves, the play, by Josefina Lopez. Performances will alternate in English and Spanish. Please only submit once for this production. Los Angeles local talent preferred. Housing and travel are not available for this project. All roles will undress to underwear, but there is no full nudity.

Rate of Pay / Contract: Minimum 1 AEA contract (not role specific) - $393.14 weekly minimum (SPT 1) and Non-union talent will fall under a volunteer agreement with $1,000 mileage reimbursement for entire period of rehearsals and performances

Additional Project Info: Rehearsals mostly weekday evenings and weekend daytimes with longer rehearsals on tech days. Additional rehearsals for Spanish language after opening of show.
Performances: Fridays and Saturdays at 8pm, Sundays at 2pm and 7pm

Roles:

[ANA] Latina, 18, plump and pretty, sister of Estela, daughter of Carmen. She is a recent high school graduate and a young feminist who wants to go to college but is stuck in the factory helping out her sister.

[ESTELA] Latina, 34, plump, plain-looking, owner of the ‚ÄúGarcia Sewing Factory‚Äù, a hopeless romantic at heart, but a hard worker.

[CARMEN] Latina, 50, a short, large woman, mother of Ana and Estela. She has a talent for storytelling and gossip.

[PANCHA] Latina, 32, a huge woman who is very mellow in her ways, but quick with her tongue, very Catholic and traditional at times.

[ROSALI] Latina, 29, thin, sweet and easygoing, but has a secret and is insecure about her sexual appeal.

STORYLINE: Set in a tiny sewing factory in East L.A., this is the outrageously funny story of five full- figured Mexican-American women who are racing to meet nearly impossible production deadlines in order to keep their tiny factory from going under. And while they work, hiding from the INS (Immigration and Naturalization Service), they talk... about their husbands and lovers, their children, their dreams for the future. The story is told from the point of view of Ana, the youngest among them. Just graduated from high school, Ana dreams of getting out of the barrio and going off to college and becoming a famous writer. Although she needs the money, Ana doesn't like working at the factory and has little respect for the coworkers, who make fun of her ambitions and what they consider her idealistic feminist philosophies. However, Ana keeps coming to her job and chronicling her experiences in a journal. As the summer unfolds, she slowly gains an understanding and appreciation of the work and the women, eventually writing an essay that wins her a journalism fellowship which will take her to New York City. This play, a microcosm of the Latina immigrant experience, celebrates real women's bodies, the power of women, and the incredible bond that happens when women work together.

Producer: Emmanuel Deleage
Artistic Director: Josefina Lopez
Director: Corky Dominguez
Writer: Josefina Lopez
Casting Director: Edward Padilla
Stage Manager: Angelica Ornelas
Audition Date(s): 2/4/2026
Callback Date(s): 2/5/2026
Rehearsal Date(s): 2/16/2026 to 3/25/2026
Preview Date(s): 3/26/2026
Opening Date(s): 3/27/2026
Closing Date(s): 5/3/2026

*DIGITAL ART OPEN-CALL OPPORTUNITY IN NYC*

Start the new year by exhibiting your work **on Madison Ave** in NYC. This one-night digital art show at a five-level speakeasy art studio inside Herbwell, seeks artworks exploring **rebirth, evolution, endings, beginnings, and transformation**. Showcase your art in the same neighborhood as monumental museums and galleries like the MoMa.

All digital mediums welcome: Digital Paintings & Illustration, 3D Modeling & Digital Sculpture, Digital Collage & Vector Art, Digital Photography, Pixel Art, GIF Art / Animation, Glitch Art, Generative Art, Augmented Reality (AR) Art, Virtual Reality (VR) Art, AI Art, Mixed Media (with digital components), Video Art & Motion Graphics, NFTs & Blockchain-Backed Works, Interactive & Installation-Based Digital Works, Derivative works (where you hold rights to exhibit), Scanned Physical Works

**Why submit?**

‚Ä¢ Showcase your work in one of NYC‚Äôs most prestigious art corridors
‚Ä¢ Photos, documentation, and press coverage included
‚Ä¢ Connect with curators, collectors, and international artists
‚Ä¢ Feature in a multi-disciplinary event blending digital art, traditional art, and live music

If your work speaks to stepping into something new ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to see it.

**Apply here:** [https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC](https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC)

You can sign up for in person auditions on our website ichthystheatre.ca under the audition tab

items.text:
Casting Call (Non-Union) for ALL AGES, ALL DEMOGRAPHICS - Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions include some scripted elements to prepare, and then some improv with prompts.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. 

All experience levels with acting are welcome. We are committed to making this a respectful and safe process, with open communication and respect for boundaries.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are January 22 to February 6, based on actor availability, but our needs are ongoing and more will occur in the future, so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is $60 CAD per hour, with the expectation of some prepared material, studio session duration: 1-2 hours. If there is some significant preparation required, compensation is offered for that time.

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume, as well as some information about you, such as gender identity, age, cultural/racial background. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again. We do sometimes receive more submissions than we are able to respond to, but we do read them all, and we do save your submissions for future consideration.

items.text:
If you‚Äôre doing a live callback online, always prep first.
Remember, first impressions count.

Before you go live do some prep !

1.Check the space and background you‚Äôre in to make sure it is clean, neutral, and distraction free

2.Test the lighting so your face is clearly lit

3.Test the sound to ensure it is clear with no echo or background noise

4.Check your internet connection

A few minutes of prep can be the difference between a smooth, confident callback and avoidable stress.

#marksummerscasting #marksummers #castingdirector #callbacks
